// Put this configuration in ~/.claude/settings.json
//
// ⚠️  Claude Code's settings.json is STRICT JSON — it does not allow comments.
//     Copy ONLY the { ... } object below (delete every "//" line) before saving,
//     or Claude Code will fail to parse the file.
//
// Claude Code (Anthropic's official CLI) talks the Anthropic Messages API and
// reads its backend + credentials from environment variables, which can be set
// here in settings.json under "env" (applied on every launch, however Claude
// Code is started).
//
// Routing:
//   - ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL points at the gateway ROOT (no trailing /v1) — the
//     Anthropic shim serves POST /v1/messages there.
//   - ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN is sent as `Authorization: Bearer <key>`. The
//     gateway's Anthropic shim accepts that as a fallback to `x-api-key`, so
//     the Bearer token works. Set it to your KIRO_GATEWAY_API_KEY value.
//     (Keep ANTHROPIC_API_KEY unset so Claude Code uses the base-URL route.)
//   - ANTHROPIC_MODEL is the main model; ANTHROPIC_SMALL_FAST_MODEL is the
//     lightweight model Claude Code uses for background tasks (titles, etc.).
//     Both must be Kiro-supported ids (auto, claude-opus-4.8, claude-sonnet-4.6).
//
// Thinking/reasoning is MODEL-DEPENDENT: kiro-cli emits it for claude-opus-4.8
// but not for claude-sonnet-4.6 (verified). The gateway surfaces it as Anthropic
// `thinking` blocks when ACP_SURFACE_THINKING=true (the gateway default).
//
// NOTE ON EFFORT: per-request `thinking.budget_tokens` from Claude Code is not
// yet wired to kiro-cli's effort control (tracked in gateway issue #59); it is
// forwarded under _meta, which kiro-cli ignores. To bias thinking depth today,
// set a session-wide default on the gateway via KIRO_ACP_EFFORT
// (low|medium|high|xhigh|max).
{
  "env": {
    "ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL": "http://127.0.0.1:8000",
    "ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN": "change-me",
    "ANTHROPIC_MODEL": "claude-opus-4.8",
    "ANTHROPIC_SMALL_FAST_MODEL": "claude-sonnet-4.6"
  }
}
